  "response": "As of now, India has not yet implemented plastic currency notes on a large scale. The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) has conducted some trials and research on polymer or plastic banknotes, but there are no immediate plans for a full transition from paper to plastic currency.\n\nSome key points:\n\n1. The RBI has explored the potential of polymer notes and conducted limited trials.\n\n2. Polymer notes are more durable, water-resistant, and have a longer lifespan compared to paper notes.\n\n3. Some countries like Australia, Canada, and the UK have already switched to polymer currency.\n\n4. While there is ongoing research, no definitive timeline has been announced for widespread adoption of plastic currency in India.\n\nIf you want the most up-to-date information, I recommend checking the latest announcements from the Reserve Bank of India or official government sources.",
